---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Cash Assistance Eligibility"
  description="Learn about eligibility for CalWORKs, SSI, General Assistance, and other cash assistance programs in the Bay Area."
>
  <section class="section">
    <div class="container-page">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <!-- Breadcrumb -->
        <nav class="mb-6 text-sm" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
          <ol class="flex items-center gap-2">
            <li>
              <a href="/eligibility" class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >Eligibility Guides</a
              >
            </li>
            <li class="text-neutral-400">/</li>
            <li class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">Cash Assistance</li>
          </ol>
        </nav>

        <h1 class="text-4xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
          Cash Assistance Programs
        </h1>
        <p class="text-lg text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-8">
          These programs provide monthly cash payments to help with living expenses when you're
          facing financial hardship, have a disability, or are caring for children.
        </p>

        <!-- Legal Disclaimer -->
        <div
          class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <strong>Disclaimer:</strong> This guide provides general information only and is not legal
            or professional advice. Eligibility requirements may vary by individual circumstances, and
            additional requirements may apply. To determine your actual eligibility, please apply directly
            to the program. Information is subject to change without notice.
          </p>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- CalWORKs Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            CalWORKs
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— Cash Aid for Families with Children (TANF/Welfare)</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            CalWORKs (California Work Opportunity and Responsibility to Kids) is California's main
            welfare program. It provides monthly cash assistance to low-income families with
            children, plus help finding work.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Basic Requirements</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Have a child under 18 in the home (or be pregnant)</li>
              <li>• Meet income and resource limits</li>
              <li>• California resident</li>
              <li>• U.S. citizen or qualified immigrant</li>
              <li>• Participate in welfare-to-work activities (job training, education, work)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              How Much You Could Get (Maximum Monthly Grants)
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• <strong>1 adult + 1 child:</strong> ~$714/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>1 adult + 2 children:</strong> ~$878/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>2 adults + 2 children:</strong> ~$1,014/month</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 mt-3">
              Amounts vary by county and may change. Actual amount depends on your income and
              circumstances.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Additional Benefits</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-2">
              CalWORKs families usually also receive:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• <strong>CalFresh</strong> (food stamps) — automatic eligibility</li>
              <li>• <strong>Medi-Cal</strong> (health insurance) — automatic eligibility</li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Childcare assistance</strong> — help paying for childcare while you work/train
              </li>
              <li>• <strong>Job training & education</strong> — welfare-to-work services</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • <strong>Online:</strong>
              <a
                href="https://benefitscal.com"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">BenefitsCal.com</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>• <strong>In person:</strong> County social services office</li>
            <li>• <strong>Phone:</strong> Contact your county office</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- SSI Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            SSI
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— Monthly Cash for Disabled, Blind & Seniors with Low Income</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Supplemental Security Income (SSI) is a federal program that provides monthly cash
            payments to people who are disabled, blind, or 65+ and have limited income and
            resources. California adds extra money on top (SSP).
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Who Qualifies</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>Disabled:</strong> Physical or mental condition that prevents substantial work
                for 12+ months
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Blind:</strong> Vision of 20/200 or less in better eye with glasses, or limited
                visual field
              </li>
              <li>• <strong>Aged:</strong> 65 years or older</li>
              <li>• Plus: Limited income and resources (assets)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              Income & Resource Limits
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• <strong>Resources:</strong> $2,000 individual / $3,000 couple</li>
              <li>• Home you live in and one vehicle usually don't count</li>
              <li>• Income reduces your SSI payment (but some income is excluded)</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              2026 Payment Amounts (Federal SSI + California SSP)
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• <strong>Individual (living independently):</strong> ~$1,183/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>Couple (living independently):</strong> ~$1,991/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>Individual (living with others):</strong> ~$1,030/month</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 mt-3">
              Amounts vary based on living situation and other income.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border-l-4 border-primary-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-6"
          >
            <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <strong>SSI recipients automatically get Medi-Cal</strong> (free health insurance) in California
              — no separate application needed.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • <strong>Online:</strong>
              <a
                href="https://www.ssa.gov/applyforbenefits"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >ssa.gov/applyforbenefits</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              • <strong>Phone:</strong>
              <a
                href="tel:1-800-772-1213"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">1-800-772-1213</a
              > (TTY: 1-800-325-0778)
            </li>
            <li>• <strong>In person:</strong> Local Social Security office</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- SSDI Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            SSDI
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— Disability Benefits Based on Work History</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            Social Security Disability Insurance (SSDI) pays benefits to people who can't work due
            to a disability AND have paid into Social Security through past work. Unlike SSI, there
            are no income or asset limits.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Who Qualifies</h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • Have a disability that prevents substantial work for 12+ months (or is terminal)
              </li>
              <li>• Worked enough years paying Social Security taxes (varies by age)</li>
              <li>• Generally need 5-10 years of work history</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              How Much You Could Get
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Based on your earnings history</li>
              <li>• Average SSDI payment: ~$1,500/month</li>
              <li>• Maximum (2026): ~$3,900/month</li>
              <li>
                • Check your estimate at <a
                  href="https://www.ssa.gov/myaccount"
                  target="_blank"
                  rel="noopener noreferrer"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                  >ssa.gov/myaccount</a
                >
              </li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div
            class="bg-primary-50 dark:bg-primary-900/20 border-l-4 border-primary-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-6"
          >
            <p class="text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <strong>SSI vs SSDI:</strong> You might qualify for both! SSI is based on need (low income/assets).
              SSDI is based on work history. Many people receive both.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>
              • <strong>Online:</strong>
              <a
                href="https://www.ssa.gov/applyfordisability"
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline"
                >ssa.gov/applyfordisability</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>
              • <strong>Phone:</strong>
              <a
                href="tel:1-800-772-1213"
                class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">1-800-772-1213</a
              >
            </li>
            <li>• <strong>In person:</strong> Local Social Security office</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- General Assistance Section -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            General Assistance (GA)
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— County Cash Aid for Adults Without Children</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            General Assistance (also called General Relief) is a county-funded program that provides
            small cash payments to very low-income adults who don't qualify for other programs like
            CalWORKs or SSI.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              Who Typically Qualifies
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>• Adults without dependent children</li>
              <li>• Very low or no income</li>
              <li>• Not receiving SSI, CalWORKs, or other cash aid</li>
              <li>• May need to be applying for SSI (if disabled)</li>
              <li>• May need to participate in work activities</li>
            </ul>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">Payment Amounts</h3>
            <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-2">
              Varies significantly by county:
            </p>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>San Francisco:</strong> ~$687/month (County Adult Assistance Programs)
              </li>
              <li>• <strong>Alameda County:</strong> ~$447/month</li>
              <li>• <strong>Other counties:</strong> Typically $200-400/month</li>
            </ul>
            <p class="text-sm text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400 mt-3">
              Contact your county for current amounts and requirements.
            </p>
          </div>

          <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">How to Apply</h3>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            <li>• Contact your county social services or human services department</li>
            <li>• Rules and application processes vary by county</li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- One-Time Emergency Help -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Emergency Cash Help
            <span class="text-lg font-normal text-neutral-500 dark:text-neutral-400"
              >— One-Time Assistance for Emergencies</span
            >
          </h2>
          <p class="text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300 mb-4">
            If you're facing an immediate crisis, there may be one-time emergency assistance
            available.
          </p>

          <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-6 mb-6">
            <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-3">
              Types of Emergency Help
            </h3>
            <ul class="space-y-2 text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
              <li>
                • <strong>CalWORKs emergency assistance:</strong> One-time help for CalWORKs-eligible
                families
              </li>
              <li>
                • <strong>Nonprofit emergency funds:</strong> Many organizations offer one-time grants
              </li>
              <li>• <strong>211:</strong> Can connect you to local emergency resources</li>
            </ul>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Bay Area County Offices -->
        <div class="mb-12">
          <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-4">
            Bay Area County Offices
          </h2>
          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4">
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">San Francisco</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Human Services Agency<br />1235 Mission St<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:415-557-5000"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">415-557-5000</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">Alameda County</h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Social Services Agency<br />Multiple locations<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:510-268-2000"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">510-268-2000</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
                Santa Clara County
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Social Services Agency<br />Multiple locations<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:408-758-3800"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">408-758-3800</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
            <div class="bg-neutral-50 dark:bg-neutral-800 rounded-lg p-4">
              <h3 class="font-semibold text-neutral-900 dark:text-white mb-2">
                Contra Costa County
              </h3>
              <p class="text-sm text-neutral-600 dark:text-neutral-300">
                Employment & Human Services<br />Multiple locations<br />
                <a
                  href="tel:877-505-4630"
                  class="text-primary-700 dark:text-primary-300 hover:underline">877-505-4630</a
                >
              </p>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <hr class="my-8 border-neutral-200 dark:border-neutral-700" />

        <!-- Final Disclaimer -->
        <div
          class="bg-amber-50 dark:bg-amber-900/20 border-l-4 border-amber-500 p-4 rounded-r-lg mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-sm text-neutral-700 dark:text-neutral-300">
            <strong>Important Notice:</strong> The information on this page is for general guidance only.
            Program requirements, payment amounts, and benefits change periodically. This is not a guarantee
            of eligibility or benefits. The only way to determine if you qualify is to apply directly
            to the relevant program. We encourage you to contact your county office or Social Security
            for personalized assistance.
          </p>
        </div>

        <!-- Back Link -->
        <div class="text-center">
          <a href="/eligibility" class="btn-secondary">
            <svg
              class="w-4 h-4 mr-2"
              fill="none"
              stroke="currentColor"
              viewBox="0 0 24 24"
              aria-hidden="true"
            >
              <path
                stroke-linecap="round"
                stroke-linejoin="round"
                stroke-width="2"
                d="M10 19l-7-7m0 0l7-7m-7 7h18"></path>
            </svg>
            Back to Eligibility Guides
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>
